def: A modified kind of telescope adapted to taking photographs ofthe sun.
A number or mark placed opposite the lower part of a letter orsymbol to distinguish the symbol; thus, a0, b1, c2, xn, have 0, 1, 2,and n as subindices.
Of or pertaining to the viscera; splanchnic.
A disseizin by one who once before was adjudged to havedassezed the same person of the same lands, etc.; also, a writ whichlay in such a case. Blackstone.
The strong double leathers by which the two parts of a flailare united. Halliwell.
One of the labial palpi of an insect. See Illust. under Labium.
Of or pertaining to Pierides or Muses.Drink deep, or taste not the Pierian spring. Pope.
A kind of oak-leaf gall. See Gall.
Gradually decreasing; past the acme, or crisis, as a distemper.Dunglison.
Lewdness; obscenity; a brothel. B. Jonson.
To induct, as a bishop, into the powers and privileges of avacant see.
